[30;1m152 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m154 | [0m[35mhigh-dimensional space into multiple subspaces, and then stores them in a tree structure.[0m
[30;1m155 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m156 | [0m[35mWhen searching for vectors, ANNOY follows the tree structure to find subspaces closer to the target [0m
[30;1m157 | [0m[35mand then compares all the vectors in these subspaces (The number of vectors being compared should no[0m
[30;1m158 | [0m[35mless than `search_k`) to obtain the final result. Obviously, when the target vector is close to the [0m
